PART 3: THE CONE CONSTRUCTION — ADDING A VERTEX
======================================================================
3-cycle C₃: H = 3, #odd_cycles = 1
Dominating cone(C₃): H = 3, #odd_cycles = 1
Dominated cone(C₃): H = 3, #odd_cycles = 1

Transitive T₃: H = 1, #odd_cycles = 0
Dominating cone(Trans₃): H = 1, #odd_cycles = 0
Dominated cone(Trans₃): H = 1, #odd_cycles = 0

CONE RESULTS:
  T          H(T)   →  H(dom_cone(T))  H(sub_cone(T))
  C₃ (cycle)   3   →  3              3
  Trans₃       1   →  1              1

  The dominating/dominated cone ALWAYS gives H = H(T) for transitive T.
  For the 3-cycle: cone increases H from 3 to 3/3.

